title: 'Rumor' has it: German shepherd wins Best in Show at Westminster Dog Show
text:
February 15, 2017 12:08am EST February 15, 2017 12:08am EST Rumor became only the second German shepherd to win the coveted Best in Show award. Madison Square garden (Getty Images) 
Updated at 12:08 a.m. ET 
Updated at 12:08 a.m. ET 
Rumor has it a German shepherd won Best in Show at the 141st Westminster Dog Show â and that's exactly who did. 
Rumor (official name "Lockenhaus' Rumor Has It V Kenlyn") on Tuesday became only the second German shepherd to win the award in the history of the Westminster Dog Show. The first was "Covy Tucker Hill's Manhattan" in the 1987 competition.
